That the views of Davenant were such as bear the name of sub- lapsarian Calvinism‚ all his writings prove* It has, however, been said, that with respect to the doctrine of Universal Redemp- tion, he was led by Abp. This is distinctly stated by Baxter; and from this it has been inferred by many, that the views of Davenant underwent a change, and that he declined to the opinion that redemption is attainable by all.
